After installing extension, put LoHa file in your sd/models/lora folder and write LoRA notation in prompt to applying LoHa. <lora:loha_name:weight>

All of my works is free. If you'd like to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. 👍

Recommended options

    • Racing competition costume :

      • ear ornament, hairclip, bandaid on face, necklace, bandeau, bracelet, open clothes, sleeveless jacket, hooded jacket, red jacket, wristband, partially unzipped, blue skirt, pleated skirt, shorts under skirt, bike shorts, sneakers

    • Steampunk :

      • official alternate costume, steampunk, single ear cover, feather ear ornament, goggles on headwear, low twintails, short twintails, bandaid on face, collared shirt, white shirt, crop top, red bandana, shoulder cutout, frilled sleeves, puffy short sleeves, fingerless gloves, brown gloves, midriff, belt, pouch, brown skirt, frilled skirt, miniskirt, black thighhighs, thighhighs under boots, brown footwear, knee boots

    • Casual :

      • casual, beanie, red headwear, ears through headwear, ear ornament, hairclip, bandaid on face, white shirt, long sleeves, sleeves past wrists, open jacket, red jacket, plaid jacket, fanny pack, denim shorts, short shorts, white footwear, sneakers

    • Tracen summer uniform :

      • bandaid on face, hairclip, ear ornament, tracen school uniform, summer uniform, serafuku, puffy short sleeves, purple bowtie, horseshoe ornament, sailor collar, sailor shirt, purple shirt, white skirt, pleated skirt, frilled skirt, miniskirt, zettai ryouiki, white thighhighs, brown footwear, loafers

Use a model derived from or mixed with animefull model.

  • Settings

    • Stable Diffusion WebUI by Automatic1111

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • I recommend kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • Use Hires.fix to get higher quality image

      • Upscaler

        • Latent, Latent (nearest-exact), Latent (bicubic antialiased) or other Latent series.

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • trained on sd-scripts by kohya_ss.

    • LyCORIS by KohakuBlueleaf

    • Thank you all a lot!

  • based on Animefull-pruned model

  • 71 images consist of

    • 4x low quality 27 images

    • 8x medium quality 17 images

    • 16x high quality 27 images

    • => 1 epoch = 676 images

  • replaced character feature tags with winning ticket \(umamusume\)

    • 1girl, red eyes, horse ears, horse girl, tail, short hair, horse tail, simple background, solo, swept bangs, animal ears, brown hair, parted bangs, black hair, bangs

    • I think these tags are the essentials of Winning Ticket or

    • unnecessary for training because of duplication.

  • resolution : 768x768 with aspect ratio bucketing.

  • other training settings is included in training_data.zip or metadata of LoRA file.

And, special thanks to my best friend. DH.

items.name: Sport Like Poses
items.description:
This is a new set of poses to the collection. This set contains a total of 30 sport like poses, Each pose has been captured from 25 different angles, giving you a wide range of options.

Please keep in mind that due to the more dynamic poses, some images may need to be resized to fit your specific needs.

All the images in the set are in png format with the background removed, making it possible to use multiple images in a single scene without worrying about overlapping backgrounds. Additionally, the Controlnet system does not require a background to use the images, so they can be imported as they are.

However, some poses may be too far from the scene and require zooming in for stable diffusion to capture them properly.

Some poses in the set, such as those with extreme angles like top-down or bottom-right upward views, may be challenging for stable diffusion to comprehend without additional prompts support. If stable diffusion is unable to understand or generate these extreme poses, it is advisable to move on and try other poses.

In this set some poses can cause stable diffusion very hard to understand for example the upside down pose is a very difficult one. You may need more experiment with poses that could be rare in the data base.

items.name: Architectural Magazine Photo Style: Better Interior embedding helper (archmagazine)
items.description:
Inspired by a medium type tag "Architectural Diggest Photo" which is recognized by Stable Diffusion, I researched architectural magazines further and trained this textual inversion to be used as a better version of that medium (example: "archmagazine photo").

Trigger word: archmagazine. Prompt archmagazine photo of or archmagazine 3d render of, etc.

This will help with the composition of the image and will influence colors. It may also navigate toward the Photo medium (data set were photos), but you can always use a strength of 0.5-0.9 if something is too much for you.

It will work best for typical rooms inside the house: Living room, bedroom, bathroom, kitchen, dining room, etc.

Enjoy your image generation and share the results with us in the comments.

items.name: David Miscavige
items.description:
David Miscavige

A lora of the dear leader, straight from the apple box.

Generation

Loading: This lora does not require any special extensions to use. Simply use with extra networks.

Model: Use with a realistic model. Example photos were made with an unreleased realism model.

Parameters: Example photos were made using cfg of 9.5, dpm++ 2m karras sampler, 20 steps, with a lora weight of 0.8. 0.75-0.95 is an ok range.

Tips from the creators

  • The lora is best used with the prompt editing feature (i.e. [CONCEPT_1:david miscavige:0.35]).

  • We find putting the trigger words second, like above, provides the best results.

  • The numerical value in the square brackets depends a lot on your sampler and number of steps. Read the wiki if you don't know how to use it.

Final notes

First, it should go without saying: don't do illegal things. If you do, we are not responsible for it.

This lora was a large group effort that is still ongoing. We hope to get even better quality with future versions as parameters and datasets are tweaked.

Please feel free to share what you make with this. We would love to see it.

If you like it, we would appreciate telling a friend.

We hope you have as much fun with this as we had making it.

Much love,

- The Nullity Group ༼∩ •́ ヮ •̀ ༽⊃━☆ﾟ. * ･ ｡ﾟ

Here we have out Favorite Okonomiyaki chef. Personality wise she is probably the best of the three fiancees. I had evaded doing Ukyo due to her being a bit plain. She is plain not in a bad way but in a generic girl next door way. I am sure you can make a good facsimile using long hair, hair bow and brown hair. So I focused a bit more on her attire. I seem to have completed the main female cast Ranma, Kasumi, Shampoo, Akane and Nabiki.

The LORA seems mostly resilient on all the spectrum, getting too cartoonish at about .9

Had good results with: masterpiece, best_quality, highres, <lora:KuonjiUkyo:0.7>, KuonjiUkyo, large_breasts, hair_bow, brown_hair,

Her available outfits are:

  • UkyoOutfit

  • ovaDress

  • FurinkanUniform

  • naked_apron

Her hair color likes to drift to reddish brown so better add brown_hair. I investigated the color of her eyes and she seems to have 3 or four during the anime series and manga covers so I leave that one to you.

Remember to remove her hair_bow when using her ovaDress which is the only occasion in which she doesn't wear it.

I also recommend to put head_out_of_frame in the negatives as i did some shenanigans to improve her FurinkanUniform

I think this is my last Ranma 1/2 LORA for a while. The only remaining female characters of note would be Hinako, Kodachi, Ranma's mom and Natsumi and Kurumi. Getting enough decent images is a bit too much. In the future if i found some good ones, I might give it a try.

items.description:
⚠warning

This is a 2"GB" Dream Booth model. Only Hammann appears! And before the Retrofit ! ! !

Not LoRA or Lycoris. Works in the same place as Checkpoint. NSFW illustrations are difficult with just prompts. Use merge, LoRA, etc.

Trigger Word

hammann_\(azur_lane\),1girl

The words are the same as LoRA and LoHa, so I will use the same explanation!

Basically, the higher the percentage, the stronger the influence.

"solo" and "white_background" are also 100% triggers, but you should use them depending on the situation. Because "white_background" is strange even though the background is the ocean, isn't it?

QA

Q. Do I need to combine Hammann's DB with LoRA?

No, it would be nice to combine Hammann DB with Concept LoRA

Q. What is version 3e6?

It's a learning rate of 3e-6. Honestly, users don't need to worry. In my environment, there are many similar DB and it is confusing, so the learning rate is the version name.

Q. Is it necessary to divide into DB, LoRA, and LoHa?

Since the number of learning is very small, it was necessary to make up for it by branching 😭

Also, LoRA and LoHa are not perfect. DB+LoRA is a good option for those who don't know "LoRA Block Weight". Of course, for advanced users, LoHa may be enough!

Q. Ret...

No Retrofit Hammann! ! It's not in the dataset!

Q. Where is the Retrofit version?

Not now 😭 I might make one someday, I might not make it 😑

items.name: Gothic Nightclub Dark Wave Electro Party LoRa
items.description:
There is a dark wave, electro, gothic nightclub lost in time, long before the advent of social media, when images used to accumulate in galleries and pages of the web 1.0. This checkpoint was trained on images from the age of the first mass-market digital cameras 30 years ago until 15 years later. The source material has been a blurry mess of low-resolution images with lots of JPEG artefacts; they’ve all been pre-processed over several iterations with different AI upscaling and artefact removal as well as face restoration systems.

The training data from 13025 images have been blended during the training process as additions to the already present similar subjects of the SD 1.5 checkpoint. A subset of the images was already in the original low-resolution versions included in SD 1.5. The result is that this checkpoint is trained to visualise epic and surreal dark wave, electro, and gothic party scenes populated with guests and visitors wearing elaborate costumes and unique clothing with the right make-up to go along for the occasion.

The training has been set up to get the general art and a static look and feel of the dataset transferred into a versatile SD 1.5 checkpoint where everything else is preserved to allow for a wide range of subjects and compositions. The checkpoint is not trained to replicate the actual persons or a precise subset of the training data. The training took 50 epochs over 1630240 iterations.

Use “GothClub2K” in your prompts to invoke attention to the training data and dataset of the subjects alongside a detailed description of what you like to visualise.

for CP see https://civitai.com/models/36430/gothic-nightclub-dark-wave-electro-party

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps,512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.5, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

items.name: AwaitingMouthLORA
items.description:
This is for women with their tongues out. It has no eye rolling and is biased towards eye contact or having eyes closed. It is biased towards closeups but can be made to do other things easily. It can be made to push mouths open much wider than ahegao lora or the popular awaitingtongue embedding. It does well with side front or top shots. It has a tendency for split tongues especially when upscaling, reduce the cfg scale, and reduce the weight on 'tongue out'

This is a LOHA trained with 16/8/4/2, lr 2e-5 and 0.8e-5 for22 epochs on a set of 50 or so carefully curated super-close cropped images, all with identical tags "1 girl, mouth open, tongue out, extreme closeup"

You need both activation tags to make it work but you can play with the strength. It works well with any model.

Future versions may offer an ahegao option.

Only Hammann appears! And before the Retrofit ! ! !

This is LoRA. LoHa and DB are uploaded at almost the same time, so please be careful not to make a mistake.

hammann_\(azur_lane\),1girl

"solo" and "white_background" are also 100% triggers, but you should use them depending on the situation. Because "white_background" is strange even though the background is the ocean, isn't it?

Q. What is version AdaFactor...?

The scheduler is different when learning.

Lion did not learn well 😭

Q. Is it necessary to divide into DB, LoRA, and LoHa?

Since the number of learning is very small, it was necessary to make up for it by branching 😭

Also, LoRA and LoHa are not perfect. DB+LoRA is a good option for those who don't know "LoRA Block Weight". Of course, for advanced users, LoHa may be enough!

Q. Ret...

No Retrofit Hammann! ! It's not in the dataset!

Not now 😭 I might make one someday, I might not make it 😑

items.name: IronCatLoRA #5 - Sphynx Cats
items.description:
IronCatLoRA #5 - Sphynx Cats

Making LoRA's is a thing I do for fun. So if you like what I do? You can help me out by just using the LoRA and leaving a review!

I like Sphynx cats, so I made a LoRA about Sphynx cats. Okay now for the nitty and gritty. This LoRA allows you to create photorealistic Sphynx cats. It also depends of course on the checkpoint you use. But e.g. in Realistic Vision the Sphynx cats look really good, but from my testing it can work on some anime based checkpoints too (some anime checkpoints can make cursed images though 💀), it's just better at realistic checkpoints. Be sure to check out my uploaded images, I've made sure to use a variety of checkpoints.

The LoRA weights that seem to give the best results are between 0.7 and 0.9, 1.0 also works, but I've noticed that it's then sometimes harder to e.g. prompt eye or skin colour. The trigger word for this LoRA is sphynx cat, these additional prompts might help you out:

  • legs and paws might help you getting their legs and paws in the image.

  • yellow eyes, blue eyes, green eyes should work, since used dataset has Sphynx cat with different eye colours.

  • tail might help you getting their tail in the image, it might also help you force a perspective where their tail is in the image.

  • full body might help you getting a Sphynx cat fully in the image.

  • looking at the camera and looking to the side might give a certain angle the Sphynx cat will look at.

  • eating out of a bowl of food might help you get an image where the Sphynx cat eats out of food bowl.

  • looking up might help you get the Sphynx cat to look up.

  • I've tagged the skin colours of the Sphynx cats in the dataset, so you might have luck using the following prompts: white skin, gray and white skin, white and spotted black skin, gray skin, black skin, brown skin, black and white skin, brown and white skin, spotted black and brown with white skin & white and brown skin.

  • wearing a collar might help you to get the Sphynx cat to wear a collar.

  • wearing a sweater and some variants on it should help you to get the Sphynx cat to wear a sweater, wearing a shirt might also work.

  • standing, laying & sitting might help you get the Sphynx cat in those positions.

To prompt this character in her gothic outfit, enter "<lora:Stocking-PSG:strength>Anarchy Stocking, gothic frilled dress, black striped thighhighs, hair bow, mary janes, ". Accessories include "striped sword, mini wings, angel wings, halo, stuffed toy, lollipop,". Prompting "lightshow background," will prompt the transformation sequence background from the show. There's also a few other small outfits trained in here as well.

This LORA looks the best at 0.6 ~ 0.8 strength in my opinion. Stocking was trained on Anythingv4.5 at Clip Skip 2. This lora works great across other models too.

LoRA model for the character Wattson from Apex Legends. Trained for 20 epochs on the Hassaku checkpoint model.

CFG scale 6-8, although you can try experimenting.

This LoRA is very NSFW friendly, but it can do SFW images just fine as well.

Sometimes multiple subjects/fractals may appear but it is rare for this to happen, and will get ironed out over the next couple updates.

How to use LoRA's in automatic1111's web-ui:

  • Update webui (use git pullor redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to select your desired weight, or leave it at the default of 1. (example: <lora:WattsonLora:1> is 1 weight, <lora:WattsonLora:0.5> is 0.5 weight)

If you like this LoRA, I would appreciate a heart as thanks :)
